UNITED STATES of America, Appellant, v. Krikor H. TOROSIAN, Appellee. No. 7824. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. April, 1935. Peirson M. Hall, U. S. Atty., and Ernest D. Fooks, Atty., Department of Justice, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellant. Alvin Gerlack, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
